{
 "_doc": "Tier-1 card fill vectors (design 2026-07-23-card-autofill-tier1 \u00a711). `tables` is the NORMATIVE copy of the brand-synonym / contains-word / month tables \u2014 each engine deep-equals its compiled-in tables against these, so drift on either side reds that side ([T14]). `selectIndexShared` = label-only <option> lists (options as plain strings; [T8] pins opt.value's attr-absent\u2192text fallback, so the value pass \u2261 the text pass and one string per option is lossless) \u2014 BOTH engines run these through their select matcher; `expected` is the 0-based option index, null = no match (safe miss, never a guess). Matching is PASS-MAJOR ([T2]): pass 1 whole-parse, 2 digit-extraction, 3 month-name (FIRST maximal ASCII-letter run, lowercased, EQUALITY against fullName/abbreviation \u2014 prefix matching forbidden, [T3]), 4 combined-expiry digits, 5 cc-type synonym-exact-else-contains-primary; the earliest pass with any match wins, options in document order within a pass. `selectIndexDom` = value\u2260text option pairs ({value,text}; within an option value is checked before text) \u2014 TS engine ONLY (Android exposes one string per option). `expiryText`/`yearText`/`monthText` = the \u00a74 text-target adapters; stored halves are canonical (expMonth 'MM', expYear 4-digit); maxLength null = undeclared (DOM -1); any case with a non-null placeholder carries tsOnly:true (core has no placeholder signal \u2014 its \u00a79 table is exactly the placeholder-null slice). The [T16] separator comes ONLY from the anchored /m{1,2}\\s*([-/.])\\s*y/i sniff on the placeholder (default '/') \u2014 never a bare contains-scan. cc-type cases carry the stored number AND its derived brand (consistent by CardNormalize.brand \u2014 each engine consumes whichever its API takes). Tier-2 (design 2026-07-23-card-autofill-tier2 \u00a71.3 [U8]): `tables.keywords` is the ORDERED [{kind, keywords}] group array \u2014 the normative name/id vocabulary; group order is load-bearing (month/year groups before the generic exp group; the TRAILING [U1] {cc-number: [creditcard]} group fires only when no specific kind matched, so bare credit_card \u2192 number while credit_card_cvv/_expiry/_type keep their specific verdicts) and BOTH engines assert SEQUENCE equality against it \u2014 kinds AND order AND contents, never per-key lookups (a per-key assert stays vacuously green on a reorder). `dateLeg` = CORE-ONLY consumer (the Android CC_EXP AUTOFILL_TYPE_DATE leg, \u00a75): expectedMs is the epoch ms of (expYear, expMonth, day 1) UTC via days-from-civil. `splitPan` = EXT-ONLY consumer (applyCardFill's split-PAN pre-pass, \u00a74/[U19]): boxes = declared maxLengths in document order (null = undeclared); every box declared 1..8 AND sum \u2265 PAN length \u2192 sequential digit chunks, final box may take a short remainder; expected null = no split (the whole-PAN fallback + fit-guard governs). dateLeg/splitPan are whole SINGLE-CONSUMER sections \u2014 the tsOnly flag has no inverse, so a mixed section would red the wrong engine.",
